Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.86,0:00:05.22,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This is...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.22,0:00:08.30,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We've been gathering what \Nare thought to be weapons
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.30,0:00:11.00,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,from among the sacred relics \Nthat have been brought up.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.49,0:00:14.18,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I-It's a mountain of treasure!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.18,0:00:17.24,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Their restoration is your sacred duty.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.24,0:00:22.06,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Easy for you to say! I'm good, but what \Nam I supposed to do without any clues...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.84,0:00:23.71,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.42,0:00:28.30,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I can see their insides!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.30,0:00:30.49,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,How awesome is that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.49,0:00:34.54,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You may do as you wish with the \Nitems that are of no use as arms.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.54,0:00:35.01,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.78,0:00:39.72,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright! Y-You can count on me!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.88,0:00:42.38,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We will.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.77,0:00:52.90,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This is really somethin'!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.90,0:00:54.44,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You come at a cheap price.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.14,0:00:56.49,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you say somethin'?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.17,0:00:59.70,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I said that you come at a cheap price.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.42,0:01:03.98,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Satisfied with what you're given...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.23,0:01:07.50,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought you were a man with \Na little more backbone...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.83,0:01:10.21,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What's this now? What do you wanna say?!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.91,0:01:12.71,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That flying Yunboro...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.07,0:01:14.97,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What about the tin can?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.97,0:01:18.91,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I need to be able to borrow its power, you see...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.91,0:01:20.64,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not seeing where this is going...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.64,0:01:26.27,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, I've grown rather \Ntired of this fleet's methods.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.51,0:01:30.86,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm returning to the pirate trade.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.38,0:01:34.74,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Right after this fleet's at the bottom of the sea...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.68,0:01:48.79,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Commander.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.97,0:01:55.26,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Would you cancel the \Nattack against Gargantia?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.99,0:01:57.11,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.35,0:01:58.74,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.74,0:02:00.88,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If you feel an affinity towards them,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.88,0:02:03.97,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,then you had best enlighten them \Nwithout a moment to lose, yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.93,0:02:08.66,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,To increase territory for \Nthe prosperity of humankind,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.66,0:02:10.52,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,we need superior people and resources.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.93,0:02:11.86,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.32,0:02:17.89,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Ledo, our mission is to bring a \Nnew sense of order to this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.89,0:02:20.53,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Then that's no different from \Nthe Galactic Alliance...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.88,0:02:23.32,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If we can't return to the front line,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.32,0:02:27.50,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,we'll make this Earth into \Nour utopia, a second Avalon.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.14,0:02:32.54,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Our rightful cause hasn't \Nchanged. Don't waver now.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.13,0:02:37.11,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.00,0:02:42.00,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Moment of Decision
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.98,0:02:56.16,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This is incredible too.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.16,0:02:58.36,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Pinion-sama. Someone would like to see you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.36,0:02:59.95,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, sure. Come on in.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.89,0:03:05.03,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,"Pinion-{\i1}sama{\i0}"?! Pretty high and mighty!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.49,0:03:07.39,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, it's you...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.39,0:03:09.59,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,They searched through all my packages without permission!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.59,0:03:12.50,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,When did you become a VIP?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.50,0:03:14.38,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not like I asked for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.38,0:03:15.22,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.26,0:03:24.43,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Avalon...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.25,0:03:26.57,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Utopia...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.81,0:03:36.32,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll make this Earth into \Nour utopia, a second Avalon.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.27,0:03:38.28,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't waver now.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.40,0:03:44.41,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Grace!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.31,0:03:48.34,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.39,0:03:54.82,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.27,0:04:00.00,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Grace is on Gargantia with Amy.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.90,0:04:05.07,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Amy...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.45,0:04:10.28,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Here he is.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.28,0:04:11.47,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Pinion!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.99,0:04:13.59,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Keep it short.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.59,0:04:16.61,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What the devil is wrong with \Nthe people of this fleet?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.22,0:04:20.63,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,They all act like ghosts.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.63,0:04:24.84,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's like their eyes are glazed over. It's weird.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.61,0:04:26.53,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, well...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.12,0:04:31.91,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,At this rate, I'm sure the same thing is \Ngoing to happen to the residents of my ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.46,0:04:36.33,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm wondering why we ever left Gargantia.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.33,0:04:38.81,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't mind the way things are going?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.69,0:04:43.97,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Someone's plotting a rebellion.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.97,0:04:44.91,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.91,0:04:45.68,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Really?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.68,0:04:48.64,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The red lobster that came to pick me up.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.05,0:04:50.79,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The Great Pirate Lukkage?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.79,0:04:53.60,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,T-Then let's work with the lobster...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.91,0:04:56.83,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,She's counting on the tin can,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.83,0:04:59.15,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,but there ain't no way Ledo would go for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.23,0:05:03.61,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But then... then we're supposed to \Nlive like this the rest of our lives?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.79,0:05:23.55,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Spread it out to collect the water!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.92,0:05:30.89,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You're soaked. You're gonna catch a cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.01,0:05:38.13,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.92,0:05:56.63,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.80,0:05:59.76,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Chamber, what's happening?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.76,0:06:03.38,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The weather phenomena called rain, \Nwhich we have observed before.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.64,0:06:06.06,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I cannot detect any particular abnormalities.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.83,0:06:21.40,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.60,0:06:27.57,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.92,0:06:42.33,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We have received a great \Nblessing from our divine god.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.10,0:06:50.72,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,They shall now make the journey to god.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.22,0:06:55.80,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We give our blessings to those who die for the sake of the living.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.39,0:06:57.85,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,W-What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.21,0:06:59.94,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop! What are you doing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.31,0:07:04.86,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,They shall be eternally honored for \Nthe salvation of the human race.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.71,0:07:24.21,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,People? Those are people, aren't they?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.41,0:07:32.81,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't come here to see this.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.64,0:07:38.34,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,They're insane...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.26,0:07:41.02,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.89,0:07:45.48,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And this insane fleet is heading next for...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.65,0:07:47.94,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,...Gargantia.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.94,0:07:49.17,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.66,0:07:57.09,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, this ain't for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.24,0:08:04.49,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I came here to protect \Neveryone from the Hideauze.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.30,0:08:07.75,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Amy... Bebel...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.80,0:08:12.34,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,To protect them all, I...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.19,0:08:55.26,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You have received orders \Nfrom Commander Kugel.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.26,0:09:00.17,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Ensign Ledo, prepare for war. \NBoard and assume battle command.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.45,0:09:05.14,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I await your decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.66,0:09:10.22,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Decision, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.01,0:09:15.36,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I make the decisions and you carry \Nthem out. That's how it always was.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.78,0:09:25.29,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But maybe I never really \Nmade any choices at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.61,0:09:31.09,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Meaning of your utterance is unclear. \NResponse to the commander's order is...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.09,0:09:33.92,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Chamber! How does your fighting \Nstrength compare to Striker's?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.47,0:09:38.09,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Unable to calculate due to lack of data.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.09,0:09:40.43,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Unable to comprehend point of the question.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.24,0:09:45.31,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Can you fight Striker?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.77,0:09:48.73,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Well?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.49,0:09:53.01,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Currently, the actions of Striker X3752
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.01,0:09:56.74,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,would not be classified \Nas Alliance military duty.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.74,0:09:59.68,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It is possible to authorize \Nengagement in battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.68,0:10:01.95,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I see. In that case...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.97,0:10:05.41,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,...can I fight the commander?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.77,0:10:08.91,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Chamber!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.42,0:10:15.26,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The answer to that question is \Nbeyond my support system function.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.26,0:10:21.14,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,In any case, combat policy formulation \Nis in your hands, Ensign.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.79,0:10:50.79,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Please. If we use a wireless, \Nit will be intercepted.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.24,0:10:54.75,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The only way is to go over and tell \Nthem directly. There's no time!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.75,0:10:57.92,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But there's no way I can carry out \Nan important role like that...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.07,0:11:02.01,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Right now, you're the only one \Nwho can fly over to Gargantia.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.32,0:11:04.60,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Please! Save everyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.01,0:11:09.81,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Fine, but you owe me one!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.67,0:11:27.64,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Chamber, prepare for war.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.64,0:11:28.33,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Roger.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.62,0:12:08.41,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Gargantia...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.42,0:12:30.63,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Melty!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.14,0:12:34.06,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It {\i1}was{\i0} you!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.78,0:12:37.06,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Amy... Amy!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.06,0:12:39.85,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Gargantia is... gonna be attacked...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.85,0:12:40.86,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Melty!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.59,0:12:46.70,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Can you believe it? She flew all \Nthe way over here on a surf kite.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.38,0:12:52.25,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Melty!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.46,0:12:55.11,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Saaya... Amy...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.20,0:13:00.92,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,In order to protect Gargantia,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.19,0:13:06.00,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,we have no choice but to do as Melty \Nsaid, changing course and evacuating.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.38,0:13:09.88,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,From my point of view, I'd have to say...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.88,0:13:10.85,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.09,0:13:12.30,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Amy!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.89,0:13:16.02,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Melty told me!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.62,0:13:20.98,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,She said Ledo is gonna let \Nus get away and then fight!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.76,0:13:22.73,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.06,0:13:26.66,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,He's gonna fight on his own, in our place!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.30,0:13:31.12,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,He's even gonna turn against an \Nold friend to protect Gargantia!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.62,0:13:33.85,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And we're just gonna run away?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.85,0:13:36.08,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You're okay with that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.04,0:13:39.54,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.93,0:13:45.72,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If that's what he's chosen,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.28,0:13:49.89,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,we have to make a choice as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.75,0:13:52.35,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Dr. Oldham...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.26,0:13:57.06,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Ridget, it seems the time \Nhas come to use that key.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.24,0:14:01.73,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Heaven's Ladder...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.58,0:14:05.69,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you serious?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.10,0:14:10.16,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,As this fleet's resident \Nsage, it is my responsibility
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.16,0:14:12.35,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,to offer counsel to the fleet commander.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.32,0:14:14.87,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That time is now.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.54,0:14:18.58,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Amy, I request your assistance as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.25,0:14:28.88,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We will make the world aware of my \Ngreat will and the grand power of god!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.15,0:14:32.55,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Here I declare the beginning \Nof a new holy war!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.02,0:14:35.19,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We will be victorious.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.60,0:14:38.31,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,To bring absolute order to this planet...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.85,0:14:44.27,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,To create a peaceful, glorious \Nutopia on this planet...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.82,0:14:48.46,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,...follow me!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.46,0:14:53.16,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It is the only path that will \Nlead to eternal happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.26,0:15:12.76,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Ledo...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.22,0:15:21.27,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Ensign Ledo. What foolishness is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.84,0:15:23.73,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You're the one that's \Nacting the fool.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.12,0:15:26.69,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hardly proper language for \Na soldier of the Alliance.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.29,0:15:30.10,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This is Earth! It's not \Nthe Galactic Alliance!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.10,0:15:32.40,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But the human race resides on this planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.40,0:15:35.53,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And their fate is our responsibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.74,0:15:38.07,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Responsibility? Wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.42,0:15:42.45,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The people living on this planet have \Nalready built their own society!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.45,0:15:44.29,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We have no reason to destroy it!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.54,0:15:48.09,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Our rightful cause hasn't \Nchanged. Don't waver now.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.19,0:16:07.06,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop! This is a battle between the gods!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.29,0:16:42.48,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,How is it so powerful?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.98,0:16:47.40,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Conjecture: Instead of an internal \Ngenerator, its energy is from an external source.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.40,0:16:49.11,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,So it's been conserving power?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.25,0:16:55.32,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Ledo.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.64,0:17:00.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Our mission is to bring a new \Nsense of order to this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.36,0:17:08.58,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Pinion?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.92,0:17:12.01,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Pinion, withdraw! This is my fight!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.01,0:17:15.22,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Up yours! You may be birds of a feather,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.22,0:17:19.05,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,but the one pretending to be a god \Npisses me off 10,000 times more!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.05,0:17:21.00,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Ready for the next one!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.50,0:17:27.97,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Kill him!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.73,0:17:31.78,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What's this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.17,0:17:40.94,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Citizens not participating in the \Nbattle, take shelter behind the bulkheads!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.28,0:17:42.83,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Prepare the lifeboats!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.92,0:17:46.33,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The main ship is this fleet's mother ship!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.54,0:17:48.79,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Be prepared for it to become a target!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.58,0:17:53.46,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,No tolerance for a rebellion! Anyone \Nwho stands against us is the enemy!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.86,0:18:18.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,H-Her!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.50,0:18:25.54,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh my. I apologize if I\N have to get a {\i1}little{\i0} rough!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.90,0:18:49.64,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You're more of a man than I thought!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.64,0:18:50.94,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,My opinion of you is revised upwards.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.94,0:18:53.86,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up! Just scatter those \Nbastards and get over here!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.86,0:18:55.32,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,My pleasure.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.92,0:19:19.30,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Having difficulty securing \Nstrategic advantage.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.63,0:19:22.21,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Suggestion: Hit-and-run tactics.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.21,0:19:25.10,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Concentrate attacks on enemy's head.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.10,0:19:27.06,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't wanna kill the commander!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.96,0:19:32.98,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Warning: Enemy maneuverability \Nis superior to mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.13,0:19:41.24,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The strong and the weak support \Neach other through rationality.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.70,0:19:45.91,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's what humans are. Am I wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.92,0:19:47.03,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Ledo!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.55,0:20:01.51,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Now!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.64,0:20:06.01,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hit 'im!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.04,0:20:11.85,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Pinion!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.08,0:20:13.44,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.13,0:20:21.03,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Maximize generator power!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.59,0:20:49.59,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Ledo, how about trying to change \Nthis planet with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.54,0:21:01.65,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Approaching the enemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.38,0:21:04.11,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Input emergency release number.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.97,0:21:07.57,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It helps that you're here.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.29,0:21:31.09,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Well? Will you follow me... again?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.36,0:21:38.98,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Commander...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.44,0:21:45.28,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Rebooting attitude control system.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.23,0:22:07.30,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Ensign Ledo, your resistance is without meaning.
